history.content: I’m looking to take CS 176 this fall (as a senior woo) but am only minoring so I do not get that extra boost into enrollment :/ I’m wondering if there may be an issue with getting into the class especially considering it wasn’t offered last fall? This class is a big reason why I’m picking up the minor overall and I was even considering declaring the major just to have better guarantee of a spot, but would it be unethical/possible to just switch back to the minor later on? Or might that just be unnecessary overall? Any input is appreciated :-)
history.subject: CS 176 Enrollment
